{"word":"G4748 - στοιχέω - stoichéō - stoy-kheh'-o - Walk","slug":"G4748","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">στοιχέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>stoichéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>stoy-kheh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Walk"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C3;&#x03C4;&#x03BF;&#x03B9;&#x03C7;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - stoicheo&#x0304;</b> - <i>stoy-kheh'-o</i><p/>From a derivative of <b>&#x03C3;&#x03C4;&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C7;&#x03C9;</b> <b>steicho&#x0304;&#x0304;</b> (to <i>range</i> in regular line); to <i>march</i> in (military) rank (<i>keep step</i>), that is, (figuratively) to <i>conform</i> to virtue and piety: - walk (orderly)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G4747\">G4747</a>, <a href=\"#/G4960\">G4960</a>"}]}